##They're still here. I'm still here

WECHAT denganqing1984

Features, here, I will share my writing, reading the book.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I received masks from my friends, one from Japan, one from Beijing and one from Tianjin. Some of the friends who sent me masks were people I'd met online but hadn't met; some had met in real life, but not so well.

But they all sent out wechat messages asking me if I needed a mask, and they can send it. Thanks to their help, I was able to ease my anxiety and that of my family while I was locked away in the countryside. Masks were plentiful, and the mother handed them out to neighbors.

Couriers don't get to our country. They get to downtown Wuxue. So the address I left was downtown at my brother's house, and every time the mask arrived, the courier put it in a delivery place, and my brother went to get it.

The first time I sent it, my brother was still out of town, so I just grabbed it. Two Times later, due to the strict control of the city, the brother kept it for himself, just as they can use.

Friends also often asked me at home, I often said very good, can stay with my parents for so long, it is equivalent to a long vacation. I also often in the circle of friends sent some fresh vegetables from the garden, also share in the riverside scenery, as if it is a comfortable life in the countryside. But anxiety is repressed.

One day I had a dream, in which I suddenly lost my job, panic, fear, restlessness... these emotions hit me again. Many years ago I often have such dreams, these years basically have not, but this nightmare again, let me feel very bitter.

In fact, in reality, I work for the company, those of us in Hubei stranded staff, are trying to help. Company officials contacted us and sent us masks so we could work from home.

The emergence of this dream, let me reflect on their own, insecurity has always been like a prisoner in the depths of the soul of the ghost. On another occasion, my mother and I went downstairs, my mother first, I followed after, she held the railing, side next side talk.

Suddenly a strong feeling of pain seized me: I will eventually be separated from my parents. This separation means that sooner or later this year I will leave the embankment and go to Beijing. It also means that we will eventually say goodbye and live in a world without them.

I was scared, so I wrote down. I try to keep track of what goes on with them. But because of the records, I was afraid. In the future, when they're gone, every detail of these records, they're gonNA stab me, aren't they?

I get caught up in this conflict from time to time, and I wish I wasn't so vulnerable. But I can't help it, sitting with them watching TV, eating with them, walking with them on the Yangtze River Levee... every minute I spend with them is both precious and sad.

Sometimes at night I write in my room and it's so quiet that I feel empty. Then I run downstairs to the front room again. My Mother is on the SOFA watching TV. My father is asleep, and the room is dark, only the light on the TV screen.

I quietly past, the mother turned his head and asked: "write tired? " I did not say, give her a pinch shoulder. When I was sure of myself, I came upstairs again. They're still here. I said to myself,. I was there, too. We're all here. If it makes me feel any better,.

Mother often came to my room to sit, I jokingly asked her: "Why don't I just stay in the room. " Mother hurriedly said: "So ok? Beijing has your life. Besides, you work well, your own family is happy, of course to go back to Beijing. "

It's not that I haven't thought about the possibility of staying home, and the longer I stay home, the better I feel about living here. I can see the rape flowers opening up a little bit, the early morning birds chirping incessantly, can eat fresh vegetables at any time..

But what about longer? What kind of work can I do back home? Can I support myself and my parents by writing? My friends, the ones I like in the city, they're all cut off. Can I really fit in? I don't know, and no one can give me an answer, only what my heart wants.

But in any case, I do not regret to come back, as the friend who sent me the mask said: "Life may be just like this once, so cherish it. "
